<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="33" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[136,775,256,472]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis box="[136,238,257,281]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,232,257,281]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">Remarks</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[243,256,256,280]" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">–</emphasis>
This species is somewhat similar to 
<emphasis box="[628,651,257,280]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">P.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Okada" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[656,774,257,280]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardua" subGenus="Phortica">
(
<emphasis box="[664,680,257,280]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">P</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[700,774,257,280]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">cardua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the morphology of arista and paramere, but can be distinguished from it by the setigerous anepisternum and the aedeagal basal bridge (in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Okada" baseAuthorityYear="1977" box="[419,526,353,376]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="33" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardua">
<emphasis box="[419,435,353,376]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[451,526,353,376]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="33">cardua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: anepisternum lacking setulae; aedeagal basal bridge with ca. 5 triangular, sclerotized teeth along margin and 2–3 apically sclerotized lobe-like processes).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
